      "modified": "1970-01-01T00:00:00.045Z",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "The machine reads the page aloud, letter for letter. Under the cipher reading you are hearing enciphered speech; under the grille reading you are hearing the rhythm a table-and-overlay produces; under the abjad reading you are hearing a real language you simply don't know. Same sound, three claims. [Read the manuscript through, page by page.](https://micahchoo.github.io/Archie/viewer/#/voynich-reading) (03 §4 cross-link AV→the narrative walk; `archie:` ref resolves to the voynich-reading exhibit — the spoken/read metaphor matches the narrative spine. A note-precise `…/#/a/<logicalId>` target awaits a stable R2 note id — human/Studio follow-up.)",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        }
      ],
      "motivation": "commenting",
      "archie:hasHistory": "https://micahchoo.github.io/Archie/viewer/published/voynich-reading/annotations/history/000000001DA7BY0FQRZMH7S7C9.json"
    },
    {
